        </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/21/02 10:50:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Court of Appeals</span><hr size=1> ::Hades had watched the entire situation unfold from his scrying pool.  He shook his head angrily, as he raised his fist and slammed it onto the edge of pool::<br>
<br>
&quot;Enough!&quot;<br>
<br>
::The entire Underworld shook as Hades' anger had finally boiled over.  He raised his fist again and the Underworld shook harder::<br>
<br>
::At the place where the Olympians were meeting and having this &quot;trial&quot;, the ground shook.  It started splitting open as Hades, in all his glory emerged.  His pale skin and white hair, were offset by his black toga, and his obsidian eyes.  The silver circlet around his head was a go between on the colors.  Hades could usually be more subtle and emerge from the shadows.  Not today.  He wanted to make a statement.  And he was here to make it::<br>
<br>
&quot;Enough!&quot;  ::He growled at the Olympians::<br>
<br>
&quot;I can not allow this mockery to continue any further!&quot;<br>
<br>
::Hades rarely got involved in Olympian politics, but they were now messing with somebody under his jurisdiction.  After all, Hypnos' permament home was in the Underworld::<br>
<br>
&quot;Who are you to pass judgement upon Hypnos?&quot;  ::He looked at every single being in the room.  His voice was cold, dark.  As Hades' mood grew darker, so did the lighting in the room::<br>
<br>
&quot;There are but three people who remotely have any right to pass judgement upon anyone.  And they sit right there.  ::Hades then pointed directly at the Erinyes::<br>
<br>
&quot;So apparently Hypnos is on 'Trial' for causing a War among the Amazons?  Disrespecting 'elder' gods?  Overstepping his bounds?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well if causing public disturbance is a crime, burning the earth and causing war is a crime, then why is not Ares on trial.  Secondly, I have seen many instances where 'younger' gods have overstepped their bounds and insulted the 'elder' gods, and have gotten nothing more than a mere slap on the wrist.  And as far as overstepping bounds?  How EXACTLY did he overstep bounds?  If I'm not mistaken, he stayed within in jurisdiction as the 'God of Sleep'.  He gave many people a dream?  Do not all of us in some way, shape, or form use our gifts to manipulate mortals, as well as other?  And if any god or goddess has a personal beef with Hypnos.  Take up with Hypnos ALONE.  There is no need to hold council and condemn him for his action.  Now if I have misconstrued any facts or misunderstood something, now is your time to explain.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Hades was pacing around the room as he spoke his piece.  He then stood in the center of the room folding his arms.  The room got darker and darker as he spoke.  The fact that some of the gods radiated prevented darkness from completely engulfing the room::<br>
<br>
::Hades eyes once again gazed around the room.  When his gaze fell upon Gaia and Poseidon, a sneer seemed to cross his face.  The fact that Poseidon, was doing everything in his power to kiss her arse angered him.  He did not, nor would he ever, trust his grandmother Gaia.  He refuses to remember her attempts to overthrow the reign of the Olympians, by sending the Hechadonchiries as well as other monsters to fight them.  As far as he was concerend Gaia was a washed up ex-goddess trying to reclaim former glory by undermining her grandchildren:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 322<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/22/02 1:26:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Wrong Court of Appeals</span><hr size=1> Poseidon was not in the least bit shocked when Hades appeared and why would he not be, Hypnos was after all his subject! But being brothers neigh equal in power and equal in dignity, even with Zeus would not be enough to let Hades alone put an end to the trail. <br>
<br>
When Hades finished Poseidon patted Gaia's hand, smiled at her and rose to confront his brother. There, standing toe to toe the two looked almost like twins but for a few differences in the paraphernalia they wore. A grin showed on Poseidon's face, masking his true feelings, for he was slightly embarrased and indeed taken aback.<br>
<br>
His voice rolled as he spoke the words &quot;Brother its nice of you to come and stop by, but where's my hello? You seem to have forgotten your manners Hades, perhaps that is Hypnos' influence, you. But the blame for his foolishness is not on you, his crime is his own to hold.&quot;<br>
<br>
The God looked at Hypnos and then smiled evilly at him, then he turned his star-bright gaze on the dark God of the Underworld.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry bro, but it is not enough, we are the high Gods and goddesses of the Olympians, that is whom we are to make and pas judgement. Besides..&quot; and with his finger he poked Hades in the chest, &quot;you are not an Olympians by your own choice so do not come here now seeking to be the mediator of one who must be punished for hs crimes because you need him to do a job.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then Poseidons demeanor became serious and in all seriousness he spoke. &quot;Brother, I know things have happened of like to that which Hypnos has done, but Ares has paid in due retributiion for his folly in his defeats by both mortals and demi-gods alike and I'm sure I need not remind you of this. And these other beings you speak of have paid their debt by punishment by whomsoever they upset amongst us. But Hypnos is one of the greater of the lesser Gods and thus his needs must be met with a much higher and profound justification. Thus we, the Olympians must try him in accord with justice.&quot;<br>
<br>
